Washed, dried and pressed, the ECUP starches ahead with 'New York: Year Zero'!

This four-issue, B&amp;W mini was published in 1988 by Eclipse. It was written by Richard Barreiro and penciled by Juan Zanotto. Originally published in Argentina, it was translated for US release by Eclipse.

Premise? Mankind battles Venusians!

Not sure who scanned or when scanned but it may very well be the single worst job of scanning that I've ever stumbled across. That said, it was very likely done 15+ years ago when the science was just beginning, so be gentle.

Thankee kindly to the creative teams and the scanners! Gain it, give it!



